## Summary Workflow

1. Identify faulting instructions in your code
2. Include `libpfq_single.h`
3. Define `state` structure and `resume_iteration()` function in the library
4. Add `prepare_try_catch_mechanism()` and registration
5. Wrap faulting code with `TRY`/`CATCH` and `ENQUEUE()`
6. Add `FLUSH_QUEUE()` after your loop (processes remaining items)
7. Add cleanup with `unregister_and_free_arrays()`
8. Compile with `-g -no-pie` flags
9. Extract PC values from assembly
10. Update source code with PC values
11. Recompile and run

